@SpaceJosh I did a quick-and-dirty check before tweeting, and John Mankins says the ~10 cm wavelength of his point design is largely immune to rain absorption. I don’t know whether it could penetrate the densest cloud at the eruption — I meant the global dust coverage.

@VergaraLautaro I spoke with John Mankins about his point design system a couple days ago. He says it has to use wavelengths about 10cm long to avoid interaction with rain. He says it will be only a few % absorption at that wavelength. I haven’t checked the numbers but it sounded reasonable.
